{
  "text": "Dysregulation of FGFR signaling can lead to downstream activation of mitogen activated protein kinase (MAPK) and phosphoinositide-3-kinase (PI3K)/AKT pathways [CITATION_1] and it has been shown, that patients with FGFR amplifications profit from PIK3CA/AKT directed therapy with everolimus [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, FGFR amplification may confer resistance to CDK4/6 inhibitors [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
